Pages 48 through 58 in the annotated slide deck cover Scala hosting Jython.

I used Jython 2.5.3b1: http://www.jython.org/downloads.html


To compile Scalathon.scala:

scalac -cp .:/path/to/jython.jar Scalathon.scala 


To compile PythonAge.scala:

scalac -cp .:/path/to/jython.jar PythonAge.scala


To run PythonAge:

scala -cp .:/path/to/jython.jar a_la_spiewak.PythonAge